# Fix: Data Staleness, AI Model, Brief Flow, Document Upload, Email Delivery, UI Redesign

## Issues Identified

| # | Issue | Root Cause |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | Data takes 15-20s or hard refresh to show | Next.js Server Component caching — no `revalidatePath()` after mutations, no `dynamic = 'force-dynamic'` |
| 2 | AI fails: `gemini-1.5-pro is not found` | `gemini-1.5-pro` is deprecated. The `PROVIDER_MODELS` list in [ai.ts](file:///j:/PaceUp/lib/ai.ts#L13-L18) is stale |
| 3 | After AI fails, "brief already exists" on retry | Brief is created in step 1, AI runs in step 2. If AI fails, brief persists → retry blocked by 409. No retry path exists |
| 4 | Task board is empty even though brief exists | Expected when AI assignment failed. But the page shows no explanation or retry button |
| 5 | Email invitations don't reach the recipient | Resend sandbox (`onboarding@resend.dev`) only delivers to the **account owner's email**. Cannot send to arbitrary recipients without a verified domain |
| 6 | UI redesign wanted | Out of scope for this plan — handled separately via StitchMCP |

