## Proposed Changes

### Fix 1 — Data Staleness (Caching)

The root cause is that Server Components in Next.js App Router aggressively cache data fetches. When a mutation happens (create group, join, accept invite), the cached page data is stale until Next.js re-renders.

#### [MODIFY] [next.config.js](file:///j:/PaceUp/next.config.js)
No change needed here. The fix is at the page/route level.

#### [MODIFY] Dashboard pages — add `dynamic = 'force-dynamic'`
Force real-time data on pages that must always show fresh data:
- [page.tsx](file:///j:/PaceUp/app/dashboard/page.tsx) — Active/Previous Groups
- [page.tsx](file:///j:/PaceUp/app/dashboard/group/%5Bid%5D/page.tsx) — Group Dashboard (members, brief)
- [page.tsx](file:///j:/PaceUp/app/dashboard/group/%5Bid%5D/tasks/page.tsx) — Task Board
- [page.tsx](file:///j:/PaceUp/app/join/%5Bcode%5D/page.tsx) — Join page
- [layout.tsx](file:///j:/PaceUp/app/dashboard/layout.tsx) — Dashboard layout

Each file gets `export const dynamic = 'force-dynamic';` at the top.

#### [MODIFY] API mutation routes — add `revalidatePath`
After every mutation that changes data visible on a page, call `revalidatePath()`:
- [groups/route.ts](file:///j:/PaceUp/app/api/groups/route.ts) — after creating a group → revalidate `/dashboard`
- [groups/join/route.ts](file:///j:/PaceUp/app/api/groups/join/route.ts) — after join request → revalidate `/dashboard`
- [invitations/route.ts](file:///j:/PaceUp/app/api/invitations/route.ts) — after creating invite → revalidate group page
- [invitations/[id]/route.ts](file:///j:/PaceUp/app/api/invitations/%5Bid%5D/route.ts) — after accept/decline → revalidate `/dashboard` + group page
- [groups/[id]/leave/route.ts](file:///j:/PaceUp/app/api/groups/%5Bid%5D/leave/route.ts) — after leaving → revalidate `/dashboard`
- [groups/[id]/previous/route.ts](file:///j:/PaceUp/app/api/groups/%5Bid%5D/previous/route.ts) — after removing → revalidate `/dashboard`
- [briefs/route.ts](file:///j:/PaceUp/app/api/briefs/route.ts) — after creating brief → revalidate group page
- [ai/assign-tasks/route.ts](file:///j:/PaceUp/app/api/ai/assign-tasks/route.ts) — after assigning → revalidate group + tasks page
- [profile/route.ts](file:///j:/PaceUp/app/api/profile/route.ts) — after saving profile → revalidate `/dashboard`
- [tasks/route.ts](file:///j:/PaceUp/app/api/tasks/route.ts) — after status update → revalidate tasks page

#### [MODIFY] Client-side components — add `router.refresh()` after mutations
Ensure all client components call `router.refresh()` after successful API calls. Some already do, others don't (e.g., the invite panel after sending an invite).

