### Fix 3 — Brief + AI Failure Loop

The current flow: create brief → trigger AI. If AI fails, brief exists → retry blocked.

**Fix**: Make the brief submission and AI assignment **idempotent**:

#### [MODIFY] [brief/page.tsx](file:///j:/PaceUp/app/dashboard/group/%5Bid%5D/brief/page.tsx)
- On submit: first check if a brief already exists for this group (GET query). If yes, skip creation and go straight to AI assignment.
- Show "Retry AI Assignment" button when AI fails but brief exists.

#### [MODIFY] [ai/assign-tasks/route.ts](file:///j:/PaceUp/app/api/ai/assign-tasks/route.ts#L208-L213)
- Remove the `if (brief.status === "ANALYSED")` hard block.
- Instead, if status is ANALYSED, **delete existing tasks** and re-run (allow re-assignment).
- This lets the user retry after failure AND re-run if they want to regenerate tasks.

#### [MODIFY] [briefs/route.ts](file:///j:/PaceUp/app/api/briefs/route.ts)
- When a brief already exists and status is DRAFT, allow **updating** the brief fields instead of returning 409.
- Only block if status is ANALYSED (brief is locked after successful analysis).

