### Fix 5 — Email Delivery

> [!WARNING]
> **Resend sandbox limitation**: The `onboarding@resend.dev` sender can ONLY deliver to the email address associated with your Resend account. Sending to any other address will silently succeed (200 OK) but the email will NOT be delivered. This is a Resend policy, not a code bug.

**Options:**
1. **Add a verified domain in Resend** (e.g., `paceup.dev`) → change `FROM_ADDRESS` to `invite@paceup.dev`. This is the production fix.
2. **For dev/testing**, the sandbox only works if the recipient is your own Resend account email. Document this clearly in the UI.

#### [MODIFY] [email.ts](file:///j:/PaceUp/lib/email.ts)
- Use `RESEND_FROM_EMAIL` env var instead of hardcoded `onboarding@resend.dev`.
- Add response logging so failures are visible.

#### [MODIFY] [invitations/route.ts](file:///j:/PaceUp/app/api/invitations/route.ts)
- Return a warning message in the response when using the sandbox sender, so the UI can inform the user.

