### Fix 6 — Document Upload for Brief Submission

#### [MODIFY] [brief/page.tsx](file:///j:/PaceUp/app/dashboard/group/%5Bid%5D/brief/page.tsx)
Add a toggle: "Paste text" vs "Upload document". When "Upload document" is selected:
- Accept `.pdf`, `.docx`, `.txt`, `.md` files (max 5MB).
- The document gets parsed client-side (for .txt/.md) or sent to a parse API.
- Parsed text populates the four brief fields.

#### [NEW] [api/briefs/parse/route.ts](file:///j:/PaceUp/app/api/briefs/parse/route.ts)
- Accepts a file upload (FormData).
- Uses the user's AI model to parse the document into the four fields (idea, approach, deadline, scope).
- Returns the extracted fields so the user can review before submitting.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> PDF parsing requires a library. I recommend `pdf-parse` (3.7kB, no native deps). For DOCX, `mammoth` is the standard. Both are lightweight. Do you want me to install these, or should document upload only support `.txt` and `.md` files (zero deps)?

